Package bridges.game

Class Bridge

  • java.lang.Object
    • bridges.game.Bridge
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Bridge>
    public final class Bridge
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Bridge>
    Represent a bridge between two islands in the game Bridges. Defined as immutable object, following: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/imstrat.html

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo​(Bridge other)
        Compares this bridge to another.

        A bridge is less than another bridge, if is has the first islands within a sorted list of islands of both of these bridges or if the boolean value of isDouble() is less than the boolean value of the other isDouble() value.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Bridge>
        Returns:
        -1, if bridge is smaller than other, 0, if bridge equals other, +1, if bridge is greater than other.
